New file `tools/print_routing.py`:
```python
"""
Diagnostic: print which policy each FlightMode routes to — the default
checkpoint or a mode-specific expert — without running any simulation.

Run via:  python tools/print_routing.py [--model models/latest.zip]
                                         [--experts-dir models/experts]
"""

import argparse
import os
import sys

sys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))))

from controllers.mission_manager import MissionManager
from sim.flight_modes import MODE_NAMES


def main():
    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description="Print expert routing per FlightMode")
    parser.add_argument("--model", default="models/latest.zip", help="Default policy checkpoint")
    parser.add_argument("--experts-dir", default="models/experts", help="Per-mode expert checkpoints dir")
    args = parser.parse_args()

    mgr = MissionManager(default_model_path=args.model, experts_dir=args.experts_dir).load()
    routing = mgr.describe_routing()

    print(f"{'MODE':<12} {'SOURCE':<8} PATH")
    for mode, info in routing.items():
        path = info["path"] or "(none — random actions)"
        print(f"{MODE_NAMES[mode]:<12} {info['source']:<8} {path}")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
```

## Commands to test
```bash
# 1. Diagnostic — current state (no experts trained yet)
venv/Scripts/python.exe tools/print_routing.py

# 2. Diagnostic — with a mode-specific expert present (simulated; real M2 experts go in models/experts/<mode>.zip)
mkdir -p models/experts && cp models/latest.zip models/experts/stabilize.zip
venv/Scripts/python.exe tools/print_routing.py
rm models/experts/stabilize.zip   # cleanup

# 3. Runtime logging in visualize.py (opt-in, default off)
# in config.txt add: log_expert_switches=true
python main.py   # mode=visualize/demo per config.txt
```

## Expected output
- Command 1: all 8 modes print `SOURCE=default`, `PATH=models/latest.zip`.
- Command 2: `STABILIZE` prints `SOURCE=expert PATH=models/experts/stabilize.zip`; the other 7 modes still print `default`.
- Command 3: with the flag off (default), visualize.py behaves exactly as before — no new prints. With it on, you get one `[VIZ] Active expert for <MODE> → <path>` line the first time each mode is hit and again only when the active path actually changes (e.g. switching to a mode that has a trained expert, or pressing 1-8 to override modes) — never on a free-running mode-to-mode switch where both sides use the same default path.

